00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:48,030
 Why didn't you tell me Hae Joon was great at basketball? 

9
00:00:48,030 --> 00:00:51,010
 I've heard parents go crazy when their children are lacking. 

10
00:00:51,010 --> 00:00:53,840
 But who knew a parent could go crazy when their children are incredible, too? 

11
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:58,030
 Can you face him every day while regretting not having sent him to America? 

12
00:00:58,030 --> 00:01:01,010
 I'll follow that Ahjusshi to America. 

13
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:03,170
 Mom was in an accident. 

14
00:01:03,170 --> 00:01:06,350
 So Hui's dad, in the driver's seat, passed away. 

15
00:01:06,350 --> 00:01:10,890
 What kind of ill-fated life is this? 

16
00:01:10,890 --> 00:01:12,390
 You're the only one. 

17
00:01:12,390 --> 00:01:16,860
 San Ha, can't you stay with your mom and So Hui? 

18
00:01:23,930 --> 00:01:26,410
Why aren't they coming?

19
00:01:29,380 --> 00:01:31,920
Have you gone crazy?

20
00:01:34,060 --> 00:01:35,500
What?

21
00:01:35,500 --> 00:01:37,800
What's going on?

22
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:39,720
Dad.

23
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:44,590
Did you tell her you're going to America?

24
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:49,180
Did you know about this, Dad?

25
00:01:50,140 --> 00:01:52,560
About Kim San Ha going to Seoul, too?

26
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:55,310
Why Seoul?

27
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,800
Is it because of your mom?

28
00:02:01,760 --> 00:02:03,160
Yes.

29
00:02:03,820 --> 00:02:08,310
I planned to tell everyone after dinner when my dad got home.

30
00:02:10,260 --> 00:02:13,360
I don't think he will let you go easily.

31
00:02:13,970 --> 00:02:15,430
Yes.

32
00:02:17,140 --> 00:02:19,200
Is that all?

33
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:23,080
He plans to leave home!

34
