72
00:05:30,380 --> 00:05:35,120
I'll talk to your uncle. End of discussion.

73
00:05:35,120 --> 00:05:37,290
But Hae Joon is leaving, too.

74
00:05:37,290 --> 00:05:41,160
We are letting him go to pursue his dream.

75
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:44,930
But how can we let you go when it's obvious you'll suffer?

76
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:55,880
Just last week, Mom tried to kill herself twice.

77
00:06:00,180 --> 00:06:03,060
You and I have both lost a loved one once.

78
00:06:04,490 --> 00:06:06,950
How can I bear it if something happens to her?

79
00:06:06,950 --> 00:06:08,390
You...

80
00:06:09,390 --> 00:06:14,310
Let's say we turn a blind eye and ignore her.

81
00:06:14,310 --> 00:06:17,200
But what if something happens to her?

82
00:06:47,310 --> 00:06:49,560
   

83
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,800
You should eat before you go.

84
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:07,310
- I'll get going, too. 
 - Sit down.

85
00:07:07,310 --> 00:07:10,470
How much longer will you get to eat a home-cooked meal?

86
00:07:12,670 --> 00:07:15,070
Will you let him go?

87
00:07:15,070 --> 00:07:17,040
I said sit down.

88
00:07:28,970 --> 00:07:30,610
Eat up for now.

89
00:07:30,610 --> 00:07:33,660
I'll pack some for Joo Won separately.

90
00:07:35,290 --> 00:07:37,870
 This is all because of you. 

91
00:07:37,870 --> 00:07:41,260
Keep building your karma with that mouth of yours.

92
00:07:43,850 --> 00:07:45,200
Hey.

93
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,430
Mind your own business.

94
00:07:54,630 --> 00:07:56,710
Darn it.

95
