00:08:19,870 --> 00:08:23,150
Mr. Yoon. I'm here.

97
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:26,740
I bought some sagol* and 6 kg of loose bones. 
  (TN: Beef bone broth) 

98
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:31,040
They're good items you can't get without connections like me.

99
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:32,660
Yes, thank you.

100
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:35,940
Give me a bowl of beef broth.

101
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:44,830
If you want to feed him tomorrow, you must boil the broth all night.

102
00:08:52,540 --> 00:08:54,650
Gosh, it's refreshing.

103
00:08:58,070 --> 00:09:00,040
Good, right?

104
00:09:09,430 --> 00:09:14,150
Just think the children went to college.

105
00:09:15,730 --> 00:09:20,550
Who'd return to this rural town with a college degree?

106
00:09:20,550 --> 00:09:22,910
Do you think they're just going to college?

107
00:09:22,910 --> 00:09:25,630
They're returning to their own families.

108
00:09:25,630 --> 00:09:29,290
Feed them the broth and send them off,

109
00:09:29,290 --> 00:09:32,030
and you should forget them.

110
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:42,790
They might be someone else's children, but you raised them for ten years.

111
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:46,340
It's natural to feel lonely after sending them off.

112
00:09:46,340 --> 00:09:48,940
They're bound to leave anyway.

113
00:09:48,940 --> 00:09:54,310
I'm telling you so you don't wait painstakingly for their return.

114
00:09:54,310 --> 00:10:00,130
What parent out there doesn't have heartaches while raising children?

115
00:10:00,870 --> 00:10:02,740
Goodness...

116
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:07,000
Why do I feel so sad?

117
00:10:10,910 --> 00:10:12,430
 When? 

118
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:15,040
- Tomorrow. 
 - That soon?

119
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,460
Hey.

120
00:10:18,460 --> 00:10:22,050
Your brother is in the office submitting an application for Seoul National University.

121
00:10:22,050 --> 00:10:24,910
And your other brother says he's pursuing basketball in America.

122
00:10:24,910 --> 00:10:26,750
Weren't they going to attend Myungju University?

123
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:28,500
"America"?

124
00:10:30,780 --> 00:10:34,000
It's okay. Distance makes the heart grow fonder.

125
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:38,350
I grew closer to my unni after she went to college in Seoul.

126
00:10:38,350 --> 00:10:40,000
That might be in your case.

127
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,910
What?

128
00:10:41,910 --> 00:10:44,930
You're her real family.

129
00:10:44,930 --> 00:10:48,680
We aren't a real family. It's different.

130
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:56,130
I mean, you always said you're family, and I could see it, too.

131
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:58,640
I insisted that we were.

132
00:10:58,640 --> 00:11:01,540
You all knew they weren't my real brothers.

133
00:11:01,540 --> 00:11:04,320
Is it a surprise that only I wasn't aware?

134
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,440
I heard you submitted an application to Seoul National University.

135
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:25,170
Have a good vacation, and I'll see you at school next year.

136
00:11:25,170 --> 00:11:26,890
We will stick together for six years.

137
00:11:26,890 --> 00:11:30,590
I must accept we need to be apart for a little while.

138
00:11:30,590 --> 00:11:33,500
The entire school knows you like Kang Hae Joon.

139
00:11:34,460 --> 00:11:36,230
I heard he's going to America.

140
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:39,110
Such a distance is hard for me, too.

141
00:11:39,110 --> 00:11:43,010
Don't you know the saying, "Out of sight, out of mind"?

142
00:11:44,900 --> 00:11:48,710
Why is that so important?

143
00:11:49,690 --> 00:11:53,640
If that's how you feel, then you never liked him that much to begin with.

144
00:12:05,950 --> 00:12:07,640
Go by yourself.

145
00:12:07,640 --> 00:12:09,460
It's not something I can resolve by myself.

146
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:11,550
We both need to be present so she can feel better.

147
00:12:11,550 --> 00:12:13,800
She even went to Seoul in case you were struggling.

148
00:12:13,800 --> 00:12:16,830
Can't you even make it to the Grade 10 classroom?

149
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:20,810
- "Seoul"? 
 - Yes, Seoul.

150
00:12:20,810 --> 00:12:22,070
She went to Seoul with whom?

151
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,600
Alone.

152
00:12:23,600 --> 00:12:25,570
You let her go to Seoul alone?

153
00:12:25,570 --> 00:12:28,220
Why are you telling me that now?

154
00:12:29,990 --> 00:12:32,380
I'll go by myself, so stay out of this.

155
00:12:38,230 --> 00:12:40,260
 Did she leave early? When? 

156
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:43,430
Just now. About three minutes ago.

157
00:12:44,080 --> 00:12:47,090
Eat this. Or you can give it to Hae Joon.

158
00:13:00,890 --> 00:13:02,490
I'm just going to give this to him.

159
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,880
Why? Because I was told to.

160
00:13:06,970 --> 00:13:11,310
Wait. Can't I just give this to Joo Won?

161
00:13:13,610 --> 00:13:17,930
Fine. I'll bid him farewell while giving him this.

162
00:13:17,930 --> 00:13:19,490
We are close enough to do that.

163
00:13:19,490 --> 00:13:21,110
Hey!

164
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:37,030
Are you okay?

165
00:13:37,030 --> 00:13:38,800
Are you okay?

166
00:13:39,390 --> 00:13:41,410
I asked you first.

167
00:13:43,330 --> 00:13:45,360
I'm okay.

168
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,290
Be more careful.

169
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:52,060
Sorry.

170
00:14:01,310 --> 00:14:03,180
These are our containers.

171
00:14:03,180 --> 00:14:06,050
Joo Won went home early.

172
00:14:06,050 --> 00:14:07,850
Didn't she eat before she left?

173
00:14:08,510 --> 00:14:09,900
I'll take it.

174
00:14:13,900 --> 00:14:18,290
I think you should eat this right away.

175
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:26,050
I heard you're going to America.

176
00:14:26,050 --> 00:14:27,450
Yes.

177
00:14:27,450 --> 00:14:29,210
When?

178
00:14:30,030 --> 00:14:31,620
From here?

179
00:14:31,620 --> 00:14:33,830
I leave here tomorrow.

180
00:14:42,820 --> 00:14:45,840
Since things turned out this way, you should confess your feelings.

181
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:47,150
What feelings?

182
00:14:47,150 --> 00:14:49,910
Tell Kim San Ha how you feel.

183
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:54,420
And if I do?

184
00:14:54,420 --> 00:14:56,590
He will probably reject you.

185
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:59,270
But at least you'll have no regrets.

186
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:04,940
Am I not good enough?

187
00:15:04,940 --> 00:15:06,700
No way.

188
00:15:06,700 --> 00:15:11,370
You're smart, kind, and you can keep a secret.

189
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:17,720
Kim San Ha and I both know you're a good person.

190
00:15:19,450 --> 00:15:21,620
But you're his younger sister's friend.

191
00:15:21,620 --> 00:15:23,810
Which makes you his younger sister.

192
00:15:26,010 --> 00:15:28,100
How could that work out...

193
00:15:28,810 --> 00:15:31,640
I'm really sorry about that.

194
00:15:37,370 --> 00:15:39,570
This will all pass.

195
00:15:39,570 --> 00:15:44,190
Just wait and see. Some incredible man might appear in your life tomorrow.

196
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:47,340
"Kim San Ha?"

197
00:15:47,340 --> 00:15:49,270
"Who is that?"

198
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:51,170
That's what you'll say.

199
00:15:53,420 --> 00:15:54,930
Here.

200
00:16:03,300 --> 00:16:05,300
See you around.

201
00:16:05,300 --> 00:16:07,740
Don't let your mom stress you out too much.

202
00:16:07,740 --> 00:16:13,160
Eat well, sleep well, and be well.

203
00:16:14,810 --> 00:16:16,400
I'm off.

204
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,880
   

205
00:16:25,560 --> 00:16:27,320
Go.

206
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:29,310
Take care!

207
00:16:41,160 --> 00:16:45,280
If he can't catch onto how I feel, he could at least stop smiling at me.

208
00:16:48,930 --> 00:16:52,410
Why did he block the ball, then?

209
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:03,300
Do you feel better after eating these things?

210
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:04,930
No.

211
00:18:06,470 --> 00:18:08,010
You're right.

212
00:18:24,790 --> 00:18:27,610
I have no memory of my mom.

213
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:32,750
I saw photos of her, but I can't remember anything.

214
00:18:34,420 --> 00:18:38,820
Even if the townspeople felt bad for me for having no mom,

215
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:43,350
I couldn't really understand why they felt that way.

216
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:47,930
Since I never thought not having a mom stopped me from

217
00:18:47,930 --> 00:18:51,260
doing something or made me feel lacking.

218
00:18:52,940 --> 00:18:55,550
Since Dad did everything for me.

219
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:59,600
Since...

220
00:19:03,060 --> 00:19:06,630
it's only natural for the two of us to live together.

221
00:19:10,210 --> 00:19:12,950
But then you guys showed up.

222
00:19:15,780 --> 00:19:18,110
I loved it.

223
00:19:19,730 --> 00:19:22,560
It used to be just the two of us eating.

224
00:19:22,560 --> 00:19:25,380
But when there were five of us at the table,

225
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:28,710
even if each person only said a few words,

226
00:19:28,710 --> 00:19:32,400
there was so much to talk about.

227
00:19:32,400 --> 00:19:35,550
♫  Even if you don't  ♫

228
00:19:35,550 --> 00:19:38,090
And I didn't have to go home to an empty house.

229
00:19:38,090 --> 00:19:40,750
♫  say where it hurts  ♫

230
00:19:40,750 --> 00:19:46,140
There were plenty of people telling me to eat.

231
00:19:46,140 --> 00:19:49,400
Now, all of that feels natural.

232
00:19:51,470 --> 00:19:56,220
I naturally thought we'd live like this forever.

233
00:20:02,740 --> 00:20:06,500
♫  While secretly following me  ♫

234
00:20:06,500 --> 00:20:08,580
When I return...

235
00:20:08,580 --> 00:20:11,990
♫  Without me knowing  ♫

236
00:20:11,990 --> 00:20:15,330
I'll do that.

237
00:20:15,330 --> 00:20:19,070
Everything you want.

238
00:20:19,070 --> 00:20:20,790
♫  Your back as you looked  ♫

239
00:20:20,790 --> 00:20:22,920
Can't you stay?

240
00:20:22,920 --> 00:20:28,240
♫  Afraid stars might pour down on your cheeks  ♫

241
00:20:29,790 --> 00:20:32,160
I'll come back for the holidays.

242
00:20:32,880 --> 00:20:37,790
If I can't make it, I'll call you every day.

243
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:42,630
What use is that?

244
00:20:42,630 --> 00:20:47,340
♫  I can't be the tree that you can take shelter under  ♫

245
00:20:47,340 --> 00:20:49,090
When I return...

246
00:20:51,250 --> 00:20:53,580
I'll never leave again.

247
00:20:54,820 --> 00:21:01,720
♫  I will always, as I have  ♫

248
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:11,370
♫  Be with you, like my breath  ♫

249
00:21:31,570 --> 00:21:33,320
You're home?

250
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,220
What?

251
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:59,390
You used a fortune.

252
00:21:59,390 --> 00:22:00,840
How did you know?

253
00:22:00,840 --> 00:22:03,650
I used up my entire savings.

254
00:22:03,650 --> 00:22:06,430
You have a rich dad now, is that it?

255
00:22:06,430 --> 00:22:09,680
Is this just pocket money now?

256
00:22:09,680 --> 00:22:11,540
Hey.

257
00:22:19,870 --> 00:22:21,350
What?

258
00:22:25,020 --> 00:22:27,570
What are you doing?

259
00:22:27,570 --> 00:22:29,970
It's not like you're taking these to America.

260
00:22:29,970 --> 00:22:31,880
Give them to me.

261
00:22:32,930 --> 00:22:34,330
This, too.

262
00:22:34,330 --> 00:22:36,720
What will you do with these?

263
00:22:36,720 --> 00:22:38,440
That, too.

264
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:47,310
Hey, this is something I used to use.

265
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:51,630
Just take good care of it until I return.

266
00:22:54,580 --> 00:22:57,160
See? I'm giving you everything.

267
00:22:58,670 --> 00:23:00,500
Are you coming back?

268
00:23:02,430 --> 00:23:06,430
You can pray I don't come back, and I'll still return.

269
00:23:06,430 --> 00:23:09,260
Why would I go through the trouble?

270
00:23:13,040 --> 00:23:14,460
Hey, but this is a bit–

271
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:15,860
