Hey.

537
00:49:52,190 --> 00:49:53,880
Hae Joon.

538
00:49:54,880 --> 00:49:56,870
Dad.

539
00:49:56,870 --> 00:49:58,420
Dad...

540
00:49:59,900 --> 00:50:02,980
You... Hae Joon.

541
00:50:03,620 --> 00:50:05,700
You're really Hae Joon, right?

542
00:50:06,450 --> 00:50:09,190
Dad!

543
00:50:09,190 --> 00:50:10,950
"Dad"?

544
00:50:14,470 --> 00:50:17,320
Ahjusshi! Ahjusshi, I'm back.

545
00:50:17,320 --> 00:50:19,390
Yes, okay.

546
00:50:19,390 --> 00:50:22,970
You should've come home if you were back.

547
00:50:22,970 --> 00:50:26,480
Excuse me, Sergeant. What should I do?

548
00:50:26,480 --> 00:50:30,630
Oh, he's like a son to me.

549
00:50:31,330 --> 00:50:33,450
"Like a son..."

550
00:50:33,450 --> 00:50:37,350
Like a daughter and son...

551
00:50:37,350 --> 00:50:41,500
Then these two are siblings, right?

552
00:50:41,500 --> 00:50:42,920
If you're family–

553
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:45,110
We aren't family.

554
00:50:48,800 --> 00:50:50,730
Do you know me?

555
00:51:25,440 --> 00:51:27,160
Yes, Professor.

556
00:51:28,380 --> 00:51:32,770
Yes, I'll visit you before I start work.

557
00:51:33,570 --> 00:51:35,140
Yes.

558
00:51:42,090 --> 00:51:45,270
   

559
00:52:03,940 --> 00:52:05,910
Yoon Joo Won.

560
00:52:16,770 --> 00:52:18,670
You must listen carefully. 
    

561
00:52:18,670 --> 00:52:21,920
It's hard to prove an attempt at robbery,

562
00:52:21,920 --> 00:52:24,770
but this is clearly trespassing.

563
00:52:24,770 --> 00:52:28,300
It's an attempt only because I stopped him.

564
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:31,750
I stopped him from committing the crime, so why does he benefit from it?

565
00:52:31,750 --> 00:52:34,830
No, that's not what happened.

566
00:52:34,830 --> 00:52:38,190
That's why you should've contacted her all this time.

567
00:52:38,190 --> 00:52:40,570
What about assault? Doesn't assault apply?

568
00:52:40,570 --> 00:52:44,050
That was by accident while trying to run away.

569
00:52:44,050 --> 00:52:45,950
You hit me more.

570
00:52:45,950 --> 00:52:48,440
W-Where? Where did she hit you?

571
00:52:48,440 --> 00:52:50,550
- Did she get you good? 
 - Here...

572
00:52:50,550 --> 00:52:53,380
Who are you worrying about right now?

573
00:52:58,570 --> 00:53:00,260
Yoon Joo Won.

574
00:53:05,200 --> 00:53:08,700
Are you okay? Are you hurt anywhere? Let me see.

575
00:53:08,700 --> 00:53:10,440
Kim San Ha?

576
00:53:12,810 --> 00:53:14,590
I'm fine.

577
00:53:15,540 --> 00:53:18,580
You... You rascal.

578
00:53:19,580 --> 00:53:23,150
Ahjusshi. Dad, you were here.

579
00:53:24,930 --> 00:53:27,190
And what are you doing here?

580
00:53:28,710 --> 00:53:31,170
Let's not do this here.

581
00:53:31,170 --> 00:53:33,200
Let's talk at home.

582
00:53:33,200 --> 00:53:34,670
Is today some special day?

583
00:53:34,670 --> 00:53:37,410
Y-Yes, let's c-clear things up and–

584
00:53:37,410 --> 00:53:41,050
W-Wait, wait. Wait, wait.

585
00:53:41,050 --> 00:53:42,940
So, earlier,

586
00:53:42,940 --> 00:53:46,040
these two...

587
00:53:46,040 --> 00:53:48,030
called him "Dad."

588
00:53:48,030 --> 00:53:50,500
And he called you "Dad."

589
00:53:50,500 --> 00:53:54,310
These two are strangers.

590
00:53:54,310 --> 00:53:58,130
Then what are you two?

591
00:53:58,130 --> 00:54:05,540
The man who just arrived, you're not related to the victim, are you?

592
00:54:05,540 --> 00:54:07,380
We aren't blood-related.

593
00:54:07,380 --> 00:54:11,100
Yes, we aren't family.

594
00:54:11,100 --> 00:54:13,480
We just used to live together.

595
00:54:13,480 --> 00:54:17,490
Aren't we strangers if we haven't seen each other for ten years?

596
00:54:22,110 --> 00:54:25,160
How could you talk to your brothers like that, no matter how upset you were?

597
00:54:25,160 --> 00:54:27,230
Why not?

598
00:54:27,230 --> 00:54:29,680
They're not strangers.

599
00:54:29,680 --> 00:54:32,520
Joo Won isn't wrong.

600
00:54:35,580 --> 00:54:38,510
You didn't visit once for ten years.

601
00:54:38,510 --> 00:54:43,490
Look. They grew so many gray hairs while you two never showed up.

602
00:54:43,490 --> 00:54:45,280
They're already old.

603
00:54:45,280 --> 00:54:46,580
I'm not.

604
00:54:46,580 --> 00:54:48,700
Don't I have enough hair for my age?

605
00:54:48,700 --> 00:54:53,640
Of course. It's still luscious and full of black hair.

606
00:54:53,640 --> 00:54:56,190
I still called regularly.

607
00:54:56,190 --> 00:54:58,300
You just never answered.

608
00:55:00,940 --> 00:55:05,460
- Me? 
 - You haven't called or texted for years.

609
00:55:06,270 --> 00:55:09,450
I was discharged last week from the military, so I haven't got a phone yet.

610
00:55:09,450 --> 00:55:11,310
- You what? 
 - What?

611
00:55:21,390 --> 00:55:24,550
 I visited the store a few times over the week. 

612
00:55:25,120 --> 00:55:27,980
 But when I thought about it, 

613
00:55:27,980 --> 00:55:32,000
 I didn't even graduate from college 

614
00:55:32,000 --> 00:55:34,570
 and quit basketball, too. 

615
00:55:34,570 --> 00:55:36,980
I didn't know what to say.

616
00:55:38,000 --> 00:55:39,700
What about before the military?

617
00:55:39,700 --> 00:55:42,560
You should've contacted me when you came to Korea.

618
00:55:42,560 --> 00:55:44,280
I would've at least visited you.

619
00:55:44,280 --> 00:55:46,460
You must've gotten vacation, too.

620
00:55:46,460 --> 00:55:48,520
You could've called us then.

621
00:55:48,520 --> 00:55:51,560
I kept pushing it, and it got harder to do.

622
00:55:51,560 --> 00:55:54,350
Forget it. Let's hurry up and go home. We'll talk at home.

623
00:55:54,350 --> 00:55:57,960
Yes. Let's go home and talk since you must be tired.

624
00:55:57,960 --> 00:56:00,190
I need to go to the store.

625
00:56:00,190 --> 00:56:03,090
Why? Come with us.

626
00:56:03,090 --> 00:56:06,880
She needs to clean up because someone made a mess.

627
00:56:06,880 --> 00:56:08,570
Should I come with you, then?

628
00:56:08,570 --> 00:56:12,430
It's fine. We met after ten years, so you should go home and catch up.

629
00:56:12,430 --> 00:56:14,970
Yes, then. Clean up and come right away.

630
00:56:14,970 --> 00:56:16,240
Let's go.

631
00:56:16,240 --> 00:56:17,860
I'll see you at home.

632
00:56:21,040 --> 00:56:23,050
I brought my car. Let me drop you off.

633
00:56:23,050 --> 00:56:26,020
It's fine. You must be tired from driving. Don't bother.

634
00:56:26,020 --> 00:56:27,560
I can just take the cab.

635
00:56:27,560 --> 00:56:29,380
I'll see you later at home.

636
00:56:53,740 --> 00:56:56,870
Hey, what's going on?

637
00:56:56,870 --> 00:56:58,960
You're not hurt anywhere, right?

638
00:56:58,960 --> 00:57:00,430
No.

639
00:57:04,500 --> 00:57:06,100
Are you happy?

640
00:57:06,960 --> 00:57:08,660
Why would I be happy?

641
00:57:08,660 --> 00:57:10,580
Kang Hae Joon... Actually,

642
00:57:10,580 --> 00:57:12,670
he's Yang Hae Joon now.

643
00:57:12,670 --> 00:57:15,640
Your first love came back. Aren't you happy?

644
00:57:15,640 --> 00:57:17,500
That was ages ago.

645
00:57:17,500 --> 00:57:19,900
I can't even remember his face.

646
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:23,330
Why did you come back to the store?

647
00:57:23,330 --> 00:57:25,720
I can just clean up here.

648
00:57:25,720 --> 00:57:29,280
Your brothers returned after ten years, which calls for a teary reunion.

649
00:57:29,280 --> 00:57:30,780
We already had a teary reunion.

650
00:57:30,780 --> 00:57:33,380
They were just different kinds of tears.

651
00:57:36,220 --> 00:57:39,600
I'll finish cleaning up here, so you can go home.

652
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:43,250
It's fine. Four hands will be faster than two.

653
00:57:44,360 --> 00:57:46,240
You don't want to go, do you?

654
00:57:46,940 --> 00:57:49,480
It's not that I don't want to go.

655
00:57:52,400 --> 00:57:56,420
It's not like I never imagined my brothers returning.

656
00:57:56,420 --> 00:57:58,420
But...

657
00:57:58,420 --> 00:58:00,000
But?

658
00:58:00,570 --> 00:58:04,600
I'm not as happy as I thought I'd be.

659
00:58:04,600 --> 00:58:08,610
- Why? 
 - They're surely the Kim San Ha and Kang...

660
00:58:08,610 --> 00:58:11,970
I mean, Yang Hae Joon I know.

661
00:58:12,670 --> 00:58:15,350
But they feel like strangers for some odd reason.

662
00:58:15,350 --> 00:58:17,530
They smell a bit different, too.

663
00:58:17,530 --> 00:58:21,230
Are you a dog? Why'd you smell them?

664
00:58:25,210 --> 00:58:27,880
Ten years passed, you know.

665
00:58:27,880 --> 00:58:30,410
Of course, you'd feel awkward and strange.

666
00:58:30,410 --> 00:58:35,740
Even blood relatives feel awkward if you haven't met them for a while.

667
00:58:35,740 --> 00:58:38,070
- Really? 
 - Yes.

668
00:59:04,800 --> 00:59:07,030
It's still the same.

669
00:59:13,980 --> 00:59:15,710
Still the same, right?

670
00:59:16,340 --> 00:59:20,820
Mr. Yoon didn't let anyone touch your room and Hae Joon's.

671
00:59:20,820 --> 00:59:24,230
So you two could come and sleep over anytime.

672
00:59:24,230 --> 00:59:26,660
I came too late, didn't I?

673
00:59:26,660 --> 00:59:29,000
All that matters is you came.

674
00:59:45,540 --> 00:59:47,290
I'm a distant relative.

675
00:59:47,290 --> 00:59:49,070
I'm the in-law's third cousin's niece.

676
00:59:49,070 --> 00:59:51,360
I feel awkward seeing my relatives after a long time,

677
00:59:51,360 --> 00:59:53,630
but I'm really glad to see them.

678
00:59:55,340 --> 00:59:56,930
Let's go.

679
01:00:02,910 --> 01:00:06,930
All right. Here's your rice.

680
01:00:07,710 --> 01:00:09,250
You, too.

681
01:00:23,130 --> 01:00:27,300
There isn't much on the table, but let's start eating.

682
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:30,370
 - Thank you for the food!  
 - Yes.

683
01:00:47,090 --> 01:00:50,440
Why? Weren't you going to eat that?

684
01:00:50,440 --> 01:00:51,940
Yes.

685
01:00:53,550 --> 01:00:55,340
Thanks.

686
01:00:56,930 --> 01:01:00,440
If you had given me a heads-up about coming, I would've gone grocery shopping.

687
01:01:00,440 --> 01:01:03,020
How is it? Is it to your liking?

688
01:01:03,020 --> 01:01:05,020
It's so delicious that I can't help it.

689
01:01:05,020 --> 01:01:07,190
Eat slowly. Take your time.

690
01:01:07,190 --> 01:01:09,200
There is a lot.

691
01:01:11,050 --> 01:01:13,300
My goodness, you look great, San Ha.

692
01:01:13,300 --> 01:01:16,180
You can get married now.

693
01:01:16,180 --> 01:01:18,790
- Are you not dating anyone? 
 - Not yet.

694
01:01:18,790 --> 01:01:23,070
A third-year resident doesn't have time to date. He barely gets any sleep.

695
01:01:23,070 --> 01:01:26,430
- It's better than my first and second year. 
 - Yes.

696
01:01:26,430 --> 01:01:32,570
Let me think about this. Hey, did we have any beer at home?

697
01:01:34,110 --> 01:01:36,250
Yes, we do.

698
01:01:45,720 --> 01:01:47,480
What about mine?

699
01:01:48,390 --> 01:01:50,490
Do you drink alcohol, too?

700
01:01:53,120 --> 01:01:56,510
She's all grown up now. Think of her age.

701
01:01:56,510 --> 01:02:00,240
All right. One for you.

702
01:02:00,240 --> 01:02:02,470
- Joo Won, too. 
 - Yes.

703
01:02:03,580 --> 01:02:05,830
- You, too. 
 - Thank you.

704
01:02:06,770 --> 01:02:09,230
- Dad. 
 - Yes.

705
01:02:14,050 --> 01:02:15,670
Allow me.

706
01:02:16,370 --> 01:02:21,760
Man, it's just like ten years ago since we're all sitting together like this.

707
01:02:21,760 --> 01:02:26,630
Since we all got together like this, let's make a toast.

708
01:02:26,630 --> 01:02:29,440
 Cheers. 

709
01:02:31,770 --> 01:02:33,740
It's nice to see you.

710
01:02:37,760 --> 01:02:39,130
What?

711
01:02:39,770 --> 01:02:41,320
It's nothing.

712
01:02:42,080 --> 01:02:50,050


713
01:02:50,690 --> 01:02:52,570
   

714
01:02:59,710 --> 01:03:02,360
- Yes. 
 -  Is it going well? 

715
01:03:02,360 --> 01:03:05,230
Not everyone can be an in-law's third cousin's niece.

716
01:03:05,230 --> 01:03:07,630
 Did you ask when they're leaving? 

717
01:03:08,600 --> 01:03:10,660
Well, I'll need to ask now.

718
01:03:10,660 --> 01:03:13,450
 Tell them to visit your store before they leave. 

719
01:03:13,450 --> 01:03:16,840
Why? You said you don't even remember Yang Hae Joon's face.

720
01:03:16,840 --> 01:03:18,850
 Well, I mean... 

721
01:03:18,850 --> 01:03:20,640
 I'm just curious. 

722
01:03:20,640 --> 01:03:22,830
Just wait for now.

723
01:03:24,010 --> 01:03:28,470
The cherries are in season, so they taste great. Help yourselves.

724
01:03:30,840 --> 01:03:33,550
You're right. They're very good.

725
01:03:34,790 --> 01:03:37,290
- Aren't they good? 
 - They're delicious.

726
01:03:38,870 --> 01:03:40,480
Join us.

727
01:03:42,130 --> 01:03:44,410
Did you two agree to come over?

728
01:03:44,410 --> 01:03:47,190
- How did you two come together like this? 
 - Exactly.

729
01:03:47,850 --> 01:03:51,130
We decided to come together since it's Joo Won's birthday.

730
01:03:52,150 --> 01:03:54,720
Why for my birthday?

731
01:03:54,720 --> 01:03:57,500
We plan to spend birthdays together from now on.

732
01:03:57,500 --> 01:03:59,260
What does that mean?

733
01:04:01,040 --> 01:04:04,560
Well, the two of us

734
01:04:04,560 --> 01:04:07,110
moved back permanently.

735
01:04:08,130 --> 01:04:10,750
We won't leave again.

736
01:04:10,750 --> 01:04:12,440
That's why we're here.

737
01:04:12,440 --> 01:04:15,670
- What? 
 - You won’t be leaving?

738
01:04:15,670 --> 01:04:18,870
We are really not leaving.

739
01:04:20,480 --> 01:04:22,310
They aren't leaving.

740
01:04:24,970 --> 01:04:30,280
Wow, my daughter's birthday will be a noisy one this year, right?

741
01:04:33,150 --> 01:04:35,210
Who said you can?

742
01:04:36,230 --> 01:04:40,230
♫  Back then, we were the world  ♫

743
01:04:40,230 --> 01:04:42,250
♫  Everything existed for us  ♫

744
01:04:42,250 --> 01:04:44,070
   

745
01:04:44,070 --> 01:04:49,610
♫  Like the sun in the clearest summer sky  ♫

746
01:04:49,610 --> 01:05:01,410
♫  We were dazzling and were united as one  ♫

